# apps/backend/src/modules/

## Responsibility
Feature-module layer for domain APIs like auth, AI, billing, flows, conversations, contacts, messaging, teams, commerce, webhooks, and admin surfaces.

## Design
Each module is a focused Elysia router, usually paired with service/model files. Cross-cutting state comes from appContext and shared lib helpers; many modules use Prisma directly for transactional work.

## Flow
Routers validate input, resolve app/organization context, call service methods, and return shaped payloads. Modules with heavy logic split orchestration into service files while keeping HTTP handlers thin.

## Integration
Modules are mounted by src/modules/index.ts into src/index.ts. They integrate with Prisma models, Redis/realtime helpers, Better Auth, and external providers such as Xendit, WhatsApp/Meta, TikTok, and S3.

